Johannesburg At least four people died and three others were in a critical condition after a taxi collided with a vehicle on the N4 near Solomon Mahlangu Drive in Pretoria on Friday, Netcare911 said. According to Netcare911, a helicopter was dispatched to airlift a minor to a trauma facility in Johannesburg for emergency medical care. &quot;The deceased are two men and two women and they were declared dead on scene by paramedics.&quot; The road was closed and motorists were advised to use alternative routes. Authorities were on scene to investigate the cause of the accident. African News Agency